look-economy-inflation-covid-stimulus-cash-hard-landing-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslowing%20US%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20hawks%20prefer%20a%20more%20conservative%20approach%2C%20reasoning%20that%20more%20than%2025%20basis%20points%20could%20signal%20that%20a%20downturn%20is%20imminent.%20The%20dovish%20side%20has%20gained%20serious%20momentum%2C%20as%20the%20odds%20of%20two%20cuts%20have%20doubled%20in%20the%20last%20week%20to%2067%25%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20CME%20FedWatch%20tool%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20that's%20still%20far%20from%20bankable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFed%20funds%20futures%20have%20never%20been%20this%20uncertain%20about%20a%20rate%20decision%20as%20they%20are%2C%20at%20least%20since%202015%2C%26quot%3B%20Bank%20of%20America%20strategists%20led%20by%20Ohsung%20Kwon%20wrote%20in%20a%20September%2016%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20turn%2C%20US%20stocks%20are%20stuck%20in%20neutral.%20Markets%20have%20tunnel%20vision%20about%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20until%20there's%20clarity%20on%20the%20Fed's%20decision%2C%20there%20isn't%20much%20logic%20in%20making%20big%20bullish%20or%20bearish%20bets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20history%20says%20investors%20can%20take%20solace%20in%20the%20fact%20that%20interest%20rates%20are%20declining%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20according%20to%20top%20minds%20at%20BMO%20Capital%20Markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBMO's%20team%20studied%20the%20eight%20monetary%20easing%20cycles%20since%201982%20and%20found%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20gained%20ground%20in%20the%2012%20months%20after%20the%20first%20cut%2075%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20rallying%20by%2011.3%25%20on%20average.%20But%20Brian%20Belski%2C%20BMO's%20chief%20investment%20strategist%2C%20noted%20that%20the%20two%20exceptions%20were%20sizable%3A%20a%2013.5%25%20loss%20after%20the%20dot-com%20bubble%20burst%2C%20and%20a%20nearly%2024%25%20slump%20during%20the%20financial%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20cycles%20where%20rate%20cuts%20were%20able%20to%20prolong%20economic%20expansion%20and%20keep%20corporate%20earnings%20on%20an%20upward%20trend%2C%20stocks%20performed%20quite%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Belski%20wrote%20in%20a%20mid-September%20note.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20in%20cycles%20where%20monetary%20stimulus%20was%20unable%20to%20prevent%20an%20economic%20downturn%20(i.e.%2C%202001%20and%202007)%2C%20stocks%20recorded%20significant%20losses%20in%20the%20following%20year%20as%20earnings%20growth%20struggled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20rate%20cuts%20aren't%20a%20cure-all%2C%20Belski%20is%20confident%20that%20the%20economic%20expansion%20will%20continue%2C%20which%20will%20keep%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks-to-buy-market-outlook-september-history-investing-strategy-bmo-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20bull%20market%20on%20firm%20footing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Although%20the%20strategy%20chief%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20softening%2C%20he%20noted%20that%20job%20additions%20are%20positive%2C%20as%20are%20estimates%20for%20corporate%20earnings%20and%20GDP%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20investor%20debate%20about%20the%20size%20and%20depth%20of%20the%20upcoming%20easing%20cycle%20somewhat%20misses%20the%20point%20%E2%80%94%20so%20long%20as%20nothing%20breaks%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20US%20stocks%20remain%20firmly%20within%20a%20bull%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Belski%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20with%20significantly%20strong%20trailing%20one-year%20performance%20headed%20into%20this%20initial%20rate%20cut%2C%20future%20gains%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20more%20muted%20relative%20to%20historical%20norms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f88380fe-1343-41b0-9952-a9ffe344eb4c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESectors%20poised%20to%20outperform%20as%20the%20Fed%20finally%20cu