%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Ftata-sons-rules-out-ipo-plans-despite-push-from-shareholder-sp-group-124091701048_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Influencer%20app%20Node's%20%2413%20million%20sale%20shows%20how%20central%20tech%20and%20AI%20have%20become%20to%20talent%20management%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222691%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Node%20cofounders%20Armin%20Faraji%20and%20Mackenzie%20D%C3%A9rival.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e87c34d17aa3c7b2b31d0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222018%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENode%20cofounders%20Armin%20Faraji%20and%20Mackenzie%20D%C3%A9rival.%3Cp%3ELuis%20Adrian%20Reyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETalent%20firm%20Dulcedo%20Group%20acquired%20influencer-marketing%20app%20Node%20in%20July%20at%20a%20%2413%20million%20valuation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20bought%20Node%20for%20its%20technological%20expertise%20and%20micro-influencer%20relationships.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20deal%20shows%20how%20central%20influencer-marketing%20tech%20has%20become%20in%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20talent-management%20agency%20Dulcedo%20Group%20acquired%20the%20influencer-marketing%20app%20Node%20in%20a%20July%20deal%20that%20valued%20the%20company%20at%20around%20%2413%20million%2C%20Node's%20cofounders%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENode%20is%20a%20mobile%20app%20that%20matches%20small%20businesses%20with%20micro%20and%20nano%20influencers%20for%20sponsored%20content%20opportunities.%20The%20company%20has%20worked%20with%20around%202%2C000%20businesses%20across%20a%20roster%20of%20around%2010%2C000%20creators%20who%20post%20promotional%20content%20in%20exchange%20for%20gifted%20products%2C%20free%20in-person%20experiences%2C%20or%20cash.%20Cofounders%20Armin%20Faraji%20and%20Mackenzie%20D%C3%A9rival%20launched%20the%20app%20in%202019.%20Node%20raised%20around%20a%20million%20dollars%20from%20angel%20investors%20and%20firms%20like%20Techstars%20and%20startup%20accelerator%20Alchemist%2C%20Faraji%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20shows%20how%20important%20tech%20products%2C%20including%20artificial-intelligence%20tools%2C%20have%20become%20in%20the%20talent%20and%20marketing%20industries.%20M%26amp%3BA%20deals%20in%20the%20category%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Facquisition-spree-in-influencer-marketing-is-bolstering-the-creator-economy-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20bustling%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20past%2012%20months%20as%20traditional%20ad%20agencies%20like%20Publicis%20Groupe%20and%20Stagwell%20have%20similarly%20added%20influencer%20startups%20to%20their%20company%20portfolios.%20Stagwell%20specifically%20called%20out%20Leaders'%20AI%20tech%20in%20its%20announcement%20around%20the%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%202008%20as%20an%20agency%20for%20more%20traditional%20media%20talent%2C%20Montreal-based%20Dulcedo%20Group%20has%20recently%20been%20on%20a%20buying%20spree%2C%20announcing%20in%20November%20it%20acquired%20creator%20talent%20agency%20Influence%2BAll%20and%20PR%20firm%20Sundae%20Creative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENode%20began%20looking%20for%20a%20buyer%20in%202023%20after%20it%20needed%20cash%20and%20ran%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcreator-economy-startups-raised-vc-money-in-bear-market-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echallenging%20fundraising%20environment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20shrunk%20its%20company%20headcount%20to%20four%20staffers%20and%20hoped%20that%20joining%20a%20larger%20agency%20could%20help%20it%20win%20deals%20with%20bigger%20brands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20realized%20that%20agencies%20are%20the%20gatekeepers%2C%26quot%3B%20D%C3%A9rival%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20would%20rather%20join%20them%20and%20help%20them%20with%20technology%20and%20that%20would%20help%20us%20with%20monetization%20and%20provide%20value%20for%20our%20investors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cofounders%20ultimately%20connected%20with%20Dulcedo%20Group%2C%20which%20put%20in%20an%20offer%20to%20acquire%20Node.%20Dulcedo%20Group%20was%20drawn%20to%20the%20company's%20technological%20expertise%20and%20roster%20of%20micro%20influencers%2C%20Faraji%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20agencies%20are%20actually%20acquiring%20technology%20from%20a%20defensive%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20Faraji%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20doing%20it%20because%20they%20are%20either%20losing%20customers%20to%20an%20influencer%20platform%20that's%20a%20tech%20startup%2C%20or%20their%20customers%20are%20coming%20to%20them%20and%20saying%2C%20'Hey%2C%20do%20you%20guys%20have%20any%20technology%3F%20The%20way%20you're%20collecting%20data%20or%20the%20way%20that%20you're%20running%20these%20campaigns%20is%20inefficient%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20drew%20us%20towards%20Dulcedo%20is%20that%20they're%20actually%20making%20acquisitions%20so%20that%20they%20can%20be%20offensive%2C%20not%20defensive.%20It's%20not%20just%20about%20protecting%20market%20share%20with%20them%2C%20it's%20about%20expanding%20market%20share%20and%20also%20addressing%20new%20customer%20segments%20within%20the%20creator%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20area%20of%20focus%20for%20Node%20post-acquisition%20is%20AI.%20The%20company%20said%20it's%20developing%20AI%20tools%20to%20improve%20social%20listening%20and%20data%20analysis%2C%20and%20streamlining%20the%20process%20of%20identifying%20new%20talent%20to%20work%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20automates%20the%20manual%20labor%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20influencer%20marketing%2C%26quot%3B%20Faraji%20said.%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20relationships%20still%20rule%20the%20industry.%20Agencies%20will%20work%20with%20creators%20that%20they%20have%20relationships%20with%2C%20and%20creators%20will%20make%20compromises%20t