%20vital%20for%20the%20West's%20internet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20threat%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-could-take-out-west-internet-gps-back-up-plan-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubsea%20cables%20the%20West%20relies%20on%20for%20the%20internet%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20growing%20more%20acute%20amid%20surveillance%20from%20a%20specialist%20undersea%20sabotage%20unit%2C%20a%20NATO%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20alliance%20was%20stepping%20up%20measures%20to%20protect%20the%20cables%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20a%20report%20that%20they're%20being%20targeted%20by%20Russia's%20General%20Staff%20Main%20Directorate%20for%20Deep%20Sea%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSince%20the%20start%20of%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20threats%20to%20subsea%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20oil%20and%20gas%20pipelines%20as%20well%20as%20data%20cables%20have%20increased%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAllies%20have%20long%20warned%20of%20the%20risk%20that%20Russian%20spy%20ships%20and%20sabotage%20vessels%20patrolling%20subsea%20cable%20routes%20could%20pose%20to%20critical%20underwater%20infrastructure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20after%20two%20US%20officials%20told%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F09%2F06%2Fpolitics%2Fus-sees-increasing-risk-of-russian-sabotage-undersea-cables%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20CNN%20on%20September%2013%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Russia%20had%20deployed%20a%20secret%20submarine%20unit%20called%20The%20General%20Staff%20Main%20Directorate%20for%20Deep%20Sea%20Research.%20Known%20by%20its%20Russian%20acronym%2C%20GUGI%2C%20the%20unit's%20goal%20is%20to%20surveil%20and%20possibly%20destroy%20the%20undersea%20cables%20the%20West%20relies%20on%20for%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cables%20run%20for%20thousands%20of%20miles%20under%20the%20ocean%20between%20Europe%20and%20North%20America%2C%20carrying%20everything%20from%20communications%20to%20streaming%20and%20financial%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Pentagon%20official%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20are%20aware%26quot%3B%20of%20these%20reports%2C%20but%20had%20nothing%20further%20to%20add%20at%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2290cbdaee-3b89-44d0-a1b4-3be5f9ec6ef8%5C%22%3EA%20unit%20specializing%20in%20undersea%20sabotage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20have%20long%20warned%20that%20the%20cables%20that%20stretch%20unprotected%20for%20thousands%20of%20miles%20underwater%20are%20exposed%20to%20being%20attacked%20and%20disabled%20by%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cables%2C%20which%20carried%20telegram%20data%20during%20World%20War%20I%2C%20have%20long%20been%20seen%20as%20military%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20world%20has%20become%20more%20dependent%20on%20internet%20data%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20disruption%20caused%20by%20sabotage%20has%20become%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20with%20relations%20between%20Russia%20and%20the%20West%20deteriorating%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20invasion%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20is%20signaling%20that%20these%20cables%20are%20a%20legitimate%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDmitry%20Medvedev%2C%20the%20deputy%20chair%20of%20Russia's%20security%20council%2C%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussias-medvedev-says-moscow-now-has-free-hand-destroy-enemies-undersea-2023-06-14%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJune%20warned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Russia%20could%20attack%20the%20cables%20in%20response%20to%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20Norstream%20pipeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20threat%20is%20not%20idle%20with%20GUGI%2C%20specifically%20formed%20for%20subversion%20back%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20reportedly%20gearing%20up%20its%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESidharth%20Kaushal%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20London's%20Rusi%20think%20tank%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20unit's%20core%20aims%20were%20%26quot%3Bsurveillance%2C%20espionage%2C%20and%20sabotage%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20operated%20not%20as%20part%20of%20the%20navy%20but%20under%20the%20direct%20command%20of%20the%20Russian%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20because%20of%20the%20sensitivity%20of%20its%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unit%20operates%20a%20small%20fleet%20of%20specialist%20deep%20water%20submarines%20capable%20of%20operating%20at%20a%20depth%20of%20around%202%2C500%20metres%20and%20a%20surveillance%20vessel%2C%20the%20Yantar%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navalnews.com%2Fnaval-news%2F2021%2F08%2Frussian-spy-ship-yantar-loitering-near-trans-atlantic-internet-cables%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20was%20spotted%20%3C%2Fa%3Enear%20sensitive%20cables%20off%20the%20UK%20coast%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussias-gugi-submarines-likely-operating-around-undersea-cables-pipelines-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20previously%20reported%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20GUGI%20appears%20to%20be%20an%20elite%20and%20difficult-to-join%20unit.%20Soviet-era%20candidates%20needed%20to%20be%20officers%20and%20have%20at%20least%20five%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20submarine%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGUGI%20members%20receive%20%26quot%3Bconsiderable%20salaries%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20organization%20treats%20their%20%26quot%3Beffective%20salaries%20as%20a%20deployment%20bonus%20related%20to%20the%20time%20they%20spend%20at%20extreme%20depths%2C%26quot%3B%20Kaushal%20said%20in%20a%20report%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%2C%20in%202012%2C%20GUGI%20personnel%20were%20earning%20600%2C000%20roubles%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20about%20%2420%2C000%2C%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fiber%20optic%20cables%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c89e2643b5e59d16b4a008%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFiber%20optic%20cables%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20Mediterranean%20Sea.%3Cp%3ESybille%20Reuter%20via%20Getty%20images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20already%20evidence%20that%20Russian%20units%20may%20have%20tampered%20with%20undersea%20cables%2C%20with%20experts%20saying%20that%20Russian%20units%20likely%20played%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.is%2FSI8xU%23selection-2369.8-2369.26%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20a%20role%20in%20the%20disappearance%20of%20miles%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20the%20cables%20near%20Lofoten%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Norway%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaushal%20said%20that%20if%20a%20direct%20conflict%20breaks%20out%20between%20Russia%20and%20a%20NATO%20state%2C%20GUGI%20would%20likely%20first%20seek%20to%20sever%20military%20cables%2C%20specifically%20those%20enabling%20the%20tracking%20of%20Russian%20military%20submarines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20could%20also%20menace%20the%20cables%20civilian%20communications%20depend%20on%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Buseful%20means%20of%20calibrated%20coercion%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20cables%20are%20exposed%20to%20damage%20in%20storms%20or%20can%20be%20accidentally%20damaged%20by%20anchors%2C%20an%20act%20of%20calculated%20sabotage%20would%20cause%20damage%20on%20a%20different%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRecovering%20from%20a%20deliberate%20sabotage%20campaign%20would%20take%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Cancian%2C%20an%20analyst%20with%20the%20CSIS%20think%20tank%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2211a9f719-8508-4515-8aa5-3b0a191b6b0b%5C%22%3ENATO%20steps%20up%20patrols%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20report%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fsafeguarding-subsea-cables-protecting-cyber-infrastructure-amid-great-power-competition%5C%22%20ta