-ai-run-web-the-truth-is-more-sinister-229609%5C%22%3Ebizarre%20AI-generated%20imagery%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20robot-like%20comments.%20You're%20lucky%20if%20your%20video%20feeds%20are%20not%20solely%20made%20up%20of%20exhortations%20to%20%E2%80%9Csubscribe%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20did%20we%20get%20here%3F%20And%20can%20we%20claw%20our%20way%20back%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommercial%20interests%20rule%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20major%20factor%20contributing%20to%20the%20current%20state%20of%20the%20internet%20is%20its%20over-commercialisation%3A%20financial%20motives%20drive%20much%20of%20the%20content.%20This%20has%20arguably%20led%20to%20the%20prevalence%20of%20sensationalism%2C%20prioritising%20virality%20over%20information%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECovert%20and%20deceptive%20advertising%20is%20widespread%2C%20blurring%20the%20line%20between%20commercial%20and%20non-commercial%20content%20to%20attract%20more%20attention%20and%20engagement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20driving%20force%20is%20the%20dominance%20of%20tech%20giants%20like%20Google%2C%20Meta%20and%20Amazon.%20They%20reach%20billions%20worldwide%20and%20wield%20immense%20power%20over%20the%20content%20we%20consume.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20platforms%20use%20advanced%20tracking%20technologies%20and%20opaque%20algorithms%20to%20generate%20hyper-targeted%20media%20content%2C%20powered%20by%20extensive%20user%20data.%20This%20creates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.campaignasia.com%2Farticle%2Fthe-echo-chamber-effect-how-algorithms-shape-our-worldview%2F491762%5C%22%3Efilter%20bubbles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20users%20are%20exposed%20to%20limited%20content%20that%20reinforces%20their%20existing%20beliefs%20and%20biases%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphilarchive.org%2Farchive%2FNGUECA%5C%22%3Eecho%20chambers%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20other%20viewpoints%20are%20actively%20discredited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBad%20actors%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FTechnology%2Fai-fuel-financial-scams-online-industry-experts%2Fstory%3Fid%3D103732051%5C%22%3Ecyber%20criminals%20and%20scammers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20an%20enduring%20problem%20online.%20However%2C%20evolving%20technology%20like%20generative%20AI%20has%20further%20empowered%20them%2C%20enabling%20them%20to%20create%20highly%20realistic%20fake%20images%2C%20deepfake%20videos%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fscience%2Fannals-of-artificial-intelligence%2Fthe-terrifying-ai-scam-that-uses-your-loved-ones-voice%5C%22%3Evoice%20cloning%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAI's%20ability%20to%20automate%20content%20creation%20has%20also%20flooded%20the%20internet%20with%20low-quality%2C%20misleading%20and%20harmful%20material%20at%20an%20unprecedented%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20sum%2C%20the%20accelerated%20commercialisation%20of%20the%20internet%2C%20the%20dominance%20of%20media%20tech%20giants%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20bad%20actors%20have%20infiltrated%20content%20on%20the%20internet.%20The%20rise%20of%20AI%20further%20intensifies%20this%2C%20making%20the%20internet%20more%20chaotic%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98good'%20internet%20remains%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20internet%E2%80%9D%20some%20of%20us%20long%20for%20with%20nostalgia%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20outset%2C%20the%20internet%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20free%20egalitarian%20space%20where%20people%20were%20meant%20to%20%E2%80%9Csurf%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cbrowse%E2%80%9D.%20Knowledge%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20shared%3A%20sites%20such%20as%20Wikipedia%20and%20The%20Internet%20Archive%20are%20continuing%20bastions%20of%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20advent%20of%20filter%20bubbles%2C%20the%20internet%20was%20a%20creative%20playground%20where%20people%20explored%20different%20ideas%2C%20discussed%20varying%20perspectives%2C%20and%20collaborated%20with%20individuals%20from%20%E2%80%9Coutgroups%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20those%20outside%20their%20social%20circles%20who%20may%20hold%20opposing%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarly%20social%20media%20platforms%20were%20built%20on%20the%20ethos%20of%20reconnecting%20with%20long-lost%20classmates%20and%20family%20members.%20Many%20of%20us%20have%20community%20groups%2C%20acquaintances%20and%20family%20we%20reach%20out%20to%20via%20the%20internet.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cconnection%E2%80%9D%20aspect%20of%20the%20internet%20remains%20as%20important%20as%20ever%20%E2%80%93%20as%20we%20all%20saw%20during%20the%20COVID%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20else%20do%20we%20want%20to%20preserve%3F%20Privacy.%20A%20New%20Yorker%20cartoon%20joke%20in%201993%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20051029045942%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.unc.edu%2Fdepts%2Fjomc%2Facademics%2Fdri%2Fidog.html%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20internet%2C%20nobody%20knows%20you're%20a%20dog%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Now%20everyone%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20advertisers%20%E2%80%93%20wants%20to%20know%20who%20you%20are.%20To%20quote%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oaic.gov.au%2Fprivacy%2Fyour-privacy-rights%2Fyour-personal-information%2Fwhat-is-privacy%5C%22%3EOffice%20of%20the%20Australian%20Information%20Commissioner%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20the%20tenets%20of%20privacy%20is%20%E2%80%9Cto%20be%20able%20to%20control%20who%20can%20see%20or%20use%20information%20about%20you%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20very%20least%2C%20we%20want%20to%20control%20what%20big%20tech%20knows%20about%20us%2C%20especially%20if%20they%20could%20stand%20to%20profit%20from%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20we%20ever%20go%20back%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20can't%20control%20%E2%80%9Ca-changin'%E2%80%9D%20times%2C%20but%20we%20can%20keep%20as%20much%20of%20the%20good%20parts%20as%20we%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20starters%2C%20we%20can%20vote%20with%20our%20feet.%20Users%20can%20enact%20change%20and%20bring%20awareness%20to%20problems%20on%20existing%20platforms.%20In%20recent%20times%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20this%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthinking-of-breaking-up-with-twitter-heres-the-right-way-to-do-it-195002%5C%22%3Eexodus%20of%20users%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20to%20other%20platforms%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economist.com%2Fthe-economist-explains%2F2023%2F06%2F26%2Fwhy-reddit-users-are-protesting-against-the-sites-leadership%5C%22%3Eplatform-wide%20protest%20against%20Reddit%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20changing%20its%20third-party%20data%20access%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20voting%20with%20our%20feet%20is%20only%20possible%20when%20there's%20competition.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20X%2C%20various%20other%20platforms%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Mastodon%20to%20Threads%20to%20Bluesky%20%E2%80%93%20enable%20users%20to%20pick%20one%20that%20aligns%20with%20their%20preferences%2C%20values%20and%20social%20circles.%20Search%20engines%20have%20alternatives%2C%20too%2C%20such%20as%20DuckDuckGo%20or%20Ecosia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20competition%20can%20only%20be%20created%20by%20moving%20to%20decentralised%20systems%20and%20removing%20monopolies.%20This%20actually%20happened%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20internet%20during%20the%201990s%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehistoryoftheweb.com%2Fbrowser-wars%2F%5C%22%3Ebrowser%20wars%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20when%20Microsoft%20was%20eventually%20accused%20of%20illegally%20monopolising%20the%20web%20browser%20market%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FUnited_States_v._Microsoft_Corp.%5C%22%3Ea%20landmark%20court%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20users%20of%20technology%2C%20all%20of%20us%20must%20remain%20vigilant%20about%20threats%20to%20our%20privacy%20and%20knowledge.%20With%20cheap%20and%20ubiquitous%20generativ