nk%5C%22%3E%20Indian%20Journal%20of%20Traditional%20Knowledge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20authors%20Dorjey%20Angchuk%20and%20Premlata%20Singh%20explain%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20melted%20snow%20water%20from%20various%20rivulets%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Ekangs-chhu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(ice%20water)%20merging%20at%20some%20point%20forms%20a%20%3Cem%3Etogpo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(stream)%20that%20flows%20through%20a%20valley%20touching%20many%20villages%20connected%20by%20the%20channel%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20(mother%20channel).%20It%20is%20built%20along%20a%20mountainside%20that%20forms%20its%20retaining%20wall%2C%20and%20is%20lined%20with%20clay%20to%20hold%20the%20water.%20This%20is%20termed%20the%20Ladakhi%20version%20of%20a%20dyke.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20some%20places%20rocks%20are%20broken%20to%20allow%20the%20passage%20of%20water%20or%20else%20where%20the%20rocks%20are%20too%20hard%2C%20a%20hollow%20poplar%20or%20willow%20trunk%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Eva-to%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20cut%20into%20two%20equal%20halves%20to%20allow%20the%20water%20easy%20passage.%20Water%20from%20the%3Cem%3E%20ma-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20further%20diverted%20into%20yu-ra%20(small%20canals)%2C%20which%20irrigates%20the%20fields.%20The%20point%20from%20where%20%3Cem%3Etogpo%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20is%20diverted%20into%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20into%20%3Cem%3Eyu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20called%20%3Cem%3Eyurgo%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20and%20ska%20is%20the%20point%20from%20where%20%3Cem%3Eyu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20is%20diverted%20to%20the%20field.%20Water%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Eska%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20further%20guided%20through%20channels%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3Esnang%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20carry%20the%20water%20into%20the%20field.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201024px)%20100vw%2C%201024px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2F03-Cultivated-land-of-sakti-Dawa-Dolma-Village-Square-1726237983.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Overview%20of%20the%20fields%20in%20Sakti%20village.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2F03-Cultivated-land-of-sakti-Dawa-Dolma-Village-Square-1726237983.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2F03-Cultivated-land-of-sakti-Dawa-Dolma-Village-Square-1726237983-300x161.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2F03-Cultivated-land-of-sakti-Dawa-Dolma-Village-Square-1726237983-500x269.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2F03-Cultivated-land-of-sakti-Dawa-Dolma-Village-Square-1726237983-768x413.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2F03-Cultivated-land-of-sakti-Dawa-Dolma-Village-Square-1726237983-150x81.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-366008%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EOverview%20of%20the%20fields%20in%20Sakti%20village.%20(Image%20courtesy%20Dawa%20Dolma%2FVillage%20Square)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20rotational%20water%20distribution%20system%20(%3Cem%3Ebandabas%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20Ladakh%20ensures%20fair%20allocation%20and%20could%20be%20studied%20and%20formalised%20in%20other%20areas%20to%20promote%20equitable%20water%20sharing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20does%20it%20work%3F%20According%20to%20Dr%20Chorol%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20%3Cem%3Ebandabas%3C%2Fem%3E%20system%20is%20a%20traditional%20method%20of%20water%20allocation%20that%20has%20been%20practised%20in%20Ladakh%20for%20centuries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20how%20it%20works%20on%20the%20ground%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVillages%20are%20divided%20into%20sections%2C%20each%20with%20a%20designated%20water%20manager%20called%20a%20%3Cem%3Echhur-pon%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWater%20from%20glacial%20streams%20is%20directed%20into%20a%20network%20of%20canals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEach%20section%20of%20the%20village%20is%20allocated%20water%20for%20irrigation%20on%20a%20rotational%20basis%2C%20typically%20for%20a%20set%20number%20of%20hours%20or%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20%3Cem%3Echhur-pon%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20responsible%20for%20opening%20and%20closing%20the%20water%20channels%20to%20ensure%20fair%20distribution.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20rotation%20is%20usually%20determined%20by%20the%20size%20of%20land%20holdings%2C%20with%20larger%20farms%20receiving%20proportionally%20more%20water%20time.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20system%20is%20flexible%20and%20can%20be%20adjusted%20based%20on%20seasonal%20water%20availability%20and%20crop%20needs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECommunity%20meetings%20are%20held%20to%20discuss%20and%20resolve%20any%20disputes%20or%20changes%20needed%20in%20the%20water%20allocation.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndigenous%20engineering%20techniques%2C%20such%20as%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20intricate%20canal%20systems%20(%3Cem%3Ema-yur%2C%20yu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20showcase%20local%20ingenuity%20in%20adapting%20to%20challenging%20terrains.%20By%20studying%20and%20applying%20such%20local%20engineering%20knowledge%2C%20we%20can%20develop%20context-appropriate%20irrigation%20solutions%20elsewhere%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20do%20these%20intricate%20canal%20systems%20work%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EMa-yur%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E(mother%20canal)%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThis%20is%20the%20main%20canal%20that%20diverts%20water%20from%20glacier-fed%20streams.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20is%20typically%20built%20along%20contour%20lines%20to%20maintain%20a%20gentle%20slope%20for%20water%20flow.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%3Cem%3E%20ma-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20often%20lined%20with%20stones%20to%20prevent%20seepage%20and%20erosion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20can%20stretch%20for%20several%20kilometres%2C%20bringing%20water%20to%20multiple%20villages.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EYu-ra%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E(subsidiary%20canals)%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThese%20are%20smaller%20channels%20that%20branch%20off%20from%20the%20ma-yur.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EYu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E%20distributes%20water%20to%20individual%20fields%20or%20clusters%20of%20fields.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20are%20designed%20to%20follow%20the%20natural%20topography%2C%20minimising%20the%20need%20for%20pumping.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFarmers%20use%20simple%20gates%20or%20stones%20to%20control%20water%20flow%20into%20their%20fields.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20systems%20allow%20locals%20to%20adapt%20to%20challenging%20terrains%20by%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUtilising%20gravity%20for%20water%20distribution%2C%20reducing%20the%20need%20for%20energy-intensive%20pumping.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMaximising%20the%20use%20of%20limited%20water%20resources%20in%20an%20arid%20environment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPreventing%20soil%20erosion%20through%20careful%20canal%20placement%20and%20construction.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAllowing%20cultivation%20on%20steep%20hillsides%20through%20terrace%20farming.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20traditional%20water%20storage%20methods%2C%20like%20the%20use%20of%20ponds%20(%3Cem%3Erdzing%3C%2Fem%3E)%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20can%20be%20revived%20and%20improved%20to%20enhance%20water%20security%20in%20water-scarce%20regions%2C%20notes%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndividual%20families%20rarely%20construct%20their%20own%20pond.%20Every%20year%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%3Cem%3E%20spit%3C%2F